caption: I really want to like this place. The food they do have is fresh and delicious, and it should be a quick healthy option. The food isn't bad, but the experience of eating at Pokeworks was disappointing.  I had a poke bowl with tuna and salmon. The tuna was fine, but the salmon was bland. My bowl had a lot of different flavors, and some of them were good.  The real issue with Pokeworks is the staff and the space. The stools are uncomfortable, and there's no room for your knees. The lighting casts weird shadows, and the staff clearly didn't want to be there.  I'd eat food from Pokeworks again, but only if I ate it somewhere else.

This food was amazing and healthy the best poke I have had. But the miso soup wasnt good at all but it says poleworks not misoworks. It was clean and the guy making the poke bowls was so friendly and creative. I told him surprise me he was knowledgeable about the products. Great personality but when I got to the register the women asked me what size I got i told her regular but then she checked with the guy that made it. I felt embarrassed and i felt my credibility was looked down upon. I'm a black women and sometimes certain area I dont feel welcome. I stood there a couple of moments while she rung up other customers that happened to be white. She never questioned them I ate my poke bowl in there by the window. I felt sad I felt like my experience was cheapened by that incident. I ate it trying to put it out my mind telling myself maybe it wasnt personal but ever since the incident I dont want to go back. I wont give my money to an establishment that doesnt honor me. I have been replaying the incident in my head ever since. It's too bad because the poke is really good I would have given it 5 stars if it wasnt for that miso soup and the incident that occurred. It may not mean anything to alot of people reading this. But it meant something to me.

Poor experience! ——————————————————————— This was our first time pokeworks and we really liked the food but was very disappointed with the staff especially the Asian girl at the end of the line/register.  The food is fresh, healthier alternative and generally better than say chipotle (and more expensive which is expected) but similar to some other negative reviews here, I asked for extra (there is no limit on add-ons according to site) and was met with an attitude by the staff.  Either charge for something extra or if there is a limit on how much you can add a topping then it must be noted clearly.

I am always wary of places that serve frozen and gassed tuna. There’s no way real quality tuna is supposed to be pink. That color is reminiscent of CO poisoning symptoms. With that in mind I opted for their salmon but the taste and texture was off. Kinda like it had been sitting around for a long while(like days) after being cut. Disappointed, if only there were a better option a couple blocks away. Maybe something way more authentic with real fresh fish cut daily. 🌈

Wanted to eat here for a while.  My wife is on the keto diet and cannot consume a lot of carbohydrates. Website states they have kale noodles but when we arrived we were informed they were "kale wheat" noodles. So we asked if we could do just seaweed salad with the poke and were told it was not possible.  When I asked if a manager could make that distinction,  we were met with a more defiant NO....so we left.  What a disappointment.
